NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|3D suggests Kerrie has an offensive hand with long diamonds and little defense against clubs and hearts and that is not what she has. So, I think pass or double is best. 3N was fine by hope, but we need to discuss the play. Hope can likely count three heart tricks if she plays the Jack because even if I have the Queen (unlikely based on the auction) she then can finesse the 9 from Eddy.|
