NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|As to the play, once the diamonds work, there is a simple way to try for an extra trick. At trick eight simply duck a club. If clubs are 3-3 you get an extra club trick. If clubs are not 3-3, you can then try for 3-3 diamonds. Therefore, there was no real fancy elimination play needed. Just simply play for one of the minors to break 3-3. In general you don't need fancy plays on most hands. Just play for suits to break normally and make sure you maximize your chances. Larry Cohen, who is one of the best US players said he rarely does end plays and squeezes. He mostly just tries to come up with several alternatives on each hand and hopes one of them works.|
